Privacy Policy
Last Updated: February 8, 2026
Introduction
This Privacy Policy describes how Pantry Planner collects, uses, and shares information when you use our mobile application (the "App").
Information We Collect
Information You Provide
Account Information: Email address, username, and password when you create an account
Saved Recipes: Recipe content, including titles, ingredients, instructions, and images that you save through the App
User-Generated Content: Notes, tags, or modifications you add to saved recipes
Automatically Collected Information
Usage Data: Information about how you interact with the App, including features used and recipes saved
Device Information: Device type, operating system, unique device identifiers
Log Data: IP address, access times, and crash reports for troubleshooting
Information from Third-Party Sources
Recipe Content: When you use our scraping feature, we retrieve publicly available recipe content from websites you provide
How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information to:
Provide, maintain, and improve the App's functionality
Create and manage your account
Store and organize your saved recipes
Generate shopping lists from recipe ingredients
Enable recipe sharing features
Respond to your support requests
Send important updates about the App (with your consent for promotional communications)
Analyze usage patterns to improve user experience
How We Share Your Information
We do not sell your personal information. We may share information in the following circumstances:
With Your Consent: When you choose to share recipes with other users
Service Providers: With third-party vendors who help us operate the App (hosting, analytics, customer support)
Legal Requirements: When required by law or to protect our rights and safety
Business Transfers: In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets
Data Storage and Security
Your data is stored on secure servers with industry-standard encryption
We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information
However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure
Your Rights and Choices
You have the right to:
Access, update, or delete your account information
Export your saved recipes
Opt out of promotional communications
Request deletion of your account and associated data
Disable certain data collection features in your device settings
To exercise these rights, contact us at Pantryplanner23@gmail.com
Third-Party Websites
When you scrape recipes from external websites, you are subject to those websites' terms of service and privacy policies. We are not responsible for the content or practices of third-party sites.
Children's Privacy
Our App is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13. If we learn we have collected such information, we will delete it promptly.
International Users
Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your own. By using the App, you consent to such transfers.
Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of significant changes by posting the new policy in the App and updating the "Last Updated" date.
Contact Us
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

Pantryplanner23@gmail.com

